# Opposition Report: Renewable Energy Facility Opposition in the United States

**Theme:** Climate & Energy Policy / Governance
**Source:** Sabin Center for Climate Change Law, Columbia University (in partnership with Prof. David E. Adelman, UT Austin)
**Geographic Coverage:** United States (all 50 states, county and municipal level)
**Time Coverage:** ~2010–present (updated monthly; latest report covers through December 31, 2024)
**Unit of Observation:** Restriction (state or local ordinance) or Contested Project
**Format:** Web (interactive map), downloadable CSV
**Access:** [oppositionreport.org](https://oppositionreport.org/reports/current/) | [Restriction data CSV](https://oppositionreport.org/wp-load.php?security_token=88698d2c95a52665&export_id=6&action=get_data) | [Contested Projects CSV](https://oppositionreport.org/wp-load.php?security_token=ba2fe335207de61e&export_id=4&action=get_data) | [June 2025 Report](https://scholarship.law.columbia.edu/sabin_climate_change/251/)
**License:** Free to access
